[OVERLAY] VimFu — :wqa / :xa — Write All + Quit
[SAY] W Q A saves all files and quits. X A is a shorter alias. One command to save everything and exit.
[SAY] You already know W A saves all, and Q A quits all. W Q A combines them. X A does the same thing with fewer keystrokes.
[SAY] X A only writes files that have actually been modified. If nothing changed, it skips the write.
[SAY] Make a change, then type X A.
[KEYS] 'o'
